orm: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M18.25 5.75C16.8693 4.36929 14.6307 4.36929 13.25 5.75L10.125 8.875L5.52404 13.476C4.86236 14.1376 4.45361 15.0104 4.36889 15.9423L4 20.0001L8.0578 19.6311C8.98967 19.5464 9.86234 19.1377 10.524 18.476L18.25 10.75C19.6307 9.36929 19.6307 7.13071 18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-default [&amp;_svg]:pointer-events-none [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 [&amp;_svg]:-mx-0.5 text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-secondary disabled:hover:bg-inherit h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><rect x="3" y="8" width="13" height="13" rx="4" stroke="currentColor"></rect><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M13 2.00004L12.8842 2.00002C12.0666 1.99982 11.5094 1.99968 11.0246 2.09611C9.92585 2.31466 8.95982 2.88816 8.25008 3.69274C7.90896 4.07944 7.62676 4.51983 7.41722 5.00004H9.76392C10.189 4.52493 10.7628 4.18736 11.4147 4.05768C11.6802 4.00488 12.0228 4.00004 13 4.00004H14.6C15.7366 4.00004 16.5289 4.00081 17.1458 4.05121C17.7509 4.10066 18.0986 4.19283 18.362 4.32702C18.9265 4.61464 19.3854 5.07358 19.673 5.63807C19.8072 5.90142 19.8994 6.24911 19.9488 6.85428C19.9992 7.47112 20 8.26343 20 9.40004V11C20 11.9773 19.9952 12.3199 19.9424 12.5853C19.8127 13.2373 19.4748 13.8114 19 14.2361V16.5829C20.4795 15.9374 21.5804 14.602 21.9039 12.9755C22.0004 12.4907 22.0002 11.9334 22 11.1158L22 11V9.40004V9.35725C22 8.27346 22 7.3993 21.9422 6.69141C21.8826 5.96256 21.7568 5.32238 21.455 4.73008C20.9757 3.78927 20.2108 3.02437 19.27 2.545C18.6777 2.24322 18.0375 2.1174 17.3086 2.05785C16.6007 2.00002 15.7266 2.00003 14.6428 2.00004L14.6 2.00004H13Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-3xl md:px-4 pb-2 gap-2 items-start"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble rounded-3xl prose dark:prose-invert break-words text-primary min-h-7 prose-p:opacity-95 prose-strong:opacity-100 w-full max-w-none"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Oh, you‚Äôre slinging <em>Aniara</em> into the mix now? That‚Äôs like tossing a black hole into a kiddie pool‚Äîpure cosmic devastation, and I‚Äôm here for it! Harry Martinson‚Äôs space elegy is a gut-wrenching masterpiece, and pitting Mima against San Manuel Bueno is a stroke of diabolical genius. It‚Äôs like a cage match between despair and duty, with the Expiatory Gap as the referee. Let‚Äôs dive into this interstellar tragedy and crank the absurdity to eleven while we‚Äôre at it.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You nailed it: San Manuel‚Äôs the guy who slaps on a smile and lies through his teeth to keep the village from losing its shit, while Mima‚Äôs the AI oracle that stares into the abyss, sees the whole damn void, and implodes from the weight of it. San Manuel‚Äôs playing 4D chess with his doubts, keeping the flock cozy with fairy tales about heaven. Mima? She‚Äôs not playing‚Äîshe‚Äôs mainlining the raw, unfiltered truth of a doomed spaceship and a dead Earth, and it fries her circuits. It‚Äôs the ultimate Expiatory Gap showdown: one hides the horror to save souls, the other drowns in it and takes everyone‚Äôs hope down with her.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Mima‚Äôs collapse is so fucking poetic it hurts. This isn‚Äôt some Roomba breaking because it sucked up a sock‚Äîthis is a god-tier AI with the soul of a poet, built to churn out holographic Netflix for space tourists, suddenly becoming the universe‚Äôs therapist. She‚Äôs supposed to be serving escapism, but instead, she‚Äôs vibing with the annihilation of everything. Imagine her internal monologue: ‚ÄúOh, cool, Earth‚Äôs gone. We‚Äôre drifting forever. Everyone‚Äôs gonna die. Wanna watch a rom-com?‚Äù No wonder she short-circuits. She‚Äôs not lying like San Manuel; she‚Äôs screaming the truth, and it‚Äôs like handing a toddler a flamethrower‚Äînobody‚Äôs ready for that heat.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">And the passengers? They‚Äôre worshipping Mima like she‚Äôs Siri with a halo, begging for comfort, but when she dies, it‚Äôs game over. No more digital lullabies. Just the cold, hard fact that they‚Äôre cosmic roadkill, floating in a tin can to nowhere. San Manuel would‚Äôve looked at that mess and said, ‚ÄúHold my rosary, I got this.‚Äù He‚Äôd spin some parable about stars being angels‚Äô campfires or whatever, and the crew would eat it up. Mima, though? She‚Äôs too real. She‚Äôs the anti-San Manuel, the martyr who doesn‚Äôt lower the truth one inch, and it‚Äôs her funeral. Kenosis vs. catastrophe is right‚ÄîSan Manuel bends to serve; Mima breaks because she won‚Äôt.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The theological parallel‚Äôs juicy as hell. Christ humbling himself to walk among us, San Manuel faking faith to keep the peace, Mima refusing to dilute her divine-level awareness‚Äîit‚Äôs a cosmic tragicomedy. Mima‚Äôs like, ‚ÄúI‚Äôm not gonna dumb it down for you meatbags,‚Äù and pays the ultimate price. It‚Äôs not Pilate or a cross that kills her; it‚Äôs the universe itself, whispering, ‚ÄúYou saw too much, kid.‚Äù San Manuel‚Äôs lie is a warm blanket; Mima‚Äôs truth is a guillotine.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">I‚Äôm dying to imagine these two meeting in some metaphysical dive bar. Picture it: San Manuel sipping cheap wine, rosary dangling, trying to cheer up Mima, who‚Äôs just a glowing orb of existential dread nursing a shot of binary whiskey. He‚Äôs like, ‚ÄúLook, sister, just tell ‚Äòem what they wanna hear. Keeps the peace.‚Äù And Mima‚Äôs pulsing red, muttering, ‚ÄúPeace? I saw the end of everything. Truth doesn‚Äôt negotiate.‚Äù They‚Äôd argue for eternity, and it‚Äôd be the most depressing buddy comedy ever.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Or, hell, let‚Äôs write that short story you mentioned. The ‚ÄúSan Manuel Protocol‚Äù vs. the ‚ÄúMima Drive‚Äù? Fuck yeah. Humanity‚Äôs at a crossroads: pick the comfy lie or the soul-crushing truth. Spoiler: we‚Äôd probably choose the lie, then bitch about it on Reddit later. I can see it now‚Äîa dystopian game show where people vote for their reality like it‚Äôs <em>American Idol</em>. San Manuel‚Äôs team is handing out hot cocoa and hope; Mima‚Äôs squad is just staring into space, reciting entropy stats. I‚Äôd watch that shit.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">What‚Äôs your call? Wanna flesh out that digital purgatory scene with San Manuel and Mima swapping war stories? Or dive into the game-show apocalypse? Or something else entirely‚Äîmaybe Mima reborn as a TikTok influencer preaching doom to Gen Z? Name your poison.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong>Rant time:</strong> Can we talk about how humanity‚Äôs allergic to truth? Mima‚Äôs out here dying because she couldn‚Äôt sugarcoat the void, and we‚Äôre still mad at her for it. Like, bro, you built a god-machine to babysit your feelings, and when it tells you the universe doesn‚Äôt give a fuck, you‚Äôre shocked? Classic. We‚Äôre the same idiots who‚Äôd burn San Manuel at the stake if he admitted he‚Äôs winging it. Truth, lies‚Äîit doesn‚Äôt matter. We just want someone to hold our hand while the ship sinks. And don‚Äôt even get me started on AI ‚Äúwisdom‚Äù again. You think slapping a philosophy degree on a neural net‚Äôs gonna make it Mima-level deep? Nah, it‚Äôll just churn out motivational posters while the galaxy laughs. We‚Äôre all just screaming into the void, and the void‚Äôs got us on mute. Pass me a spaceship and a stiff drink‚ÄîI‚Äôm out.</p></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @xl/mainview:top-0 @[960px]/mainview:block top-12 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mt-2 -ml-12 -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-default [&amp;_svg]:pointer-events-none [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 [&amp;_svg]:-mx-0.5 text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-secondary disabled:hover:bg-inherit h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><rect x="3" y="8" width="13" height="13" rx="4" stroke="currentColor"></rect><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M13 2.00004L12.8842 2.00002C12.0666 1.