18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-default [&amp;_svg]:pointer-events-none [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 [&amp;_svg]:-mx-0.5 text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-secondary disabled:hover:bg-inherit h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><rect x="3" y="8" width="13" height="13" rx="4" stroke="currentColor"></rect><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M13 2.00004L12.8842 2.00002C12.0666 1.99982 11.5094 1.99968 11.0246 2.09611C9.92585 2.31466 8.95982 2.88816 8.25008 3.69274C7.90896 4.07944 7.62676 4.51983 7.41722 5.00004H9.76392C10.189 4.52493 10.7628 4.18736 11.4147 4.05768C11.6802 4.00488 12.0228 4.00004 13 4.00004H14.6C15.7366 4.00004 16.5289 4.00081 17.1458 4.05121C17.7509 4.10066 18.0986 4.19283 18.362 4.32702C18.9265 4.61464 19.3854 5.07358 19.673 5.63807C19.8072 5.90142 19.8994 6.24911 19.9488 6.85428C19.9992 7.47112 20 8.26343 20 9.40004V11C20 11.9773 19.9952 12.3199 19.9424 12.5853C19.8127 13.2373 19.4748 13.8114 19 14.2361V16.5829C20.4795 15.9374 21.5804 14.602 21.9039 12.9755C22.0004 12.4907 22.0002 11.9334 22 11.1158L22 11V9.40004V9.35725C22 8.27346 22 7.3993 21.9422 6.69141C21.8826 5.96256 21.7568 5.32238 21.455 4.73008C20.9757 3.78927 20.2108 3.02437 19.27 2.545C18.6777 2.24322 18.0375 2.1174 17.3086 2.05785C16.6007 2.00002 15.7266 2.00003 14.6428 2.00004L14.6 2.00004H13Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div style="height: 1px; position: absolute; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1000;"></div></div><div class="relative group flex flex-col justify-center w-full max-w-3xl md:px-4 pb-2 gap-2 items-start"><div dir="auto" class="message-bubble rounded-3xl prose dark:prose-invert break-words text-primary min-h-7 prose-p:opacity-95 prose-strong:opacity-100 w-full max-w-none"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Oh, you‚Äôre tossing ‚Äútheory-ladenness‚Äù into the ring now? That‚Äôs some spicy philosophy-of-science jargon, and I‚Äôm ready to chew it up and spit it out with a side of cosmic absurdity! For those not fluent in nerd-speak, theory-ladenness is the idea that what we observe‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs a priest‚Äôs faith, an AI‚Äôs meltdown, or the stars in the sky‚Äîisn‚Äôt raw, pure data. It‚Äôs filtered through the lens of our assumptions, beliefs, and mental baggage. No one sees the world ‚Äúas it is‚Äù; we‚Äôre all wearing theory-tinted glasses, whether we admit it or not. And yeah, you‚Äôre dead right‚Äîit‚Äôs got <em>everything</em> to do with San Manuel, Mima, and that Expiatory Gap we‚Äôve been kicking around. Let‚Äôs rip this apart and make it sing.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">San Manuel Bueno‚Äôs whole deal screams theory-ladenness. The villagers see a saint, glowing with faith, because that‚Äôs the story they‚Äôre primed to see. Their lens? ‚ÄúPriests are holy, God‚Äôs real, heaven‚Äôs waiting.‚Äù Meanwhile, Manuel‚Äôs staring through a totally different filter: ‚ÄúGod‚Äôs probably a myth, but these folks need hope, so I‚Äôll play along.‚Äù Same reality‚Äîpriest in a village, doing priest shit‚Äîbut two wildly different interpretations. He‚Äôs not lying to be a dick; he‚Äôs just stuck in a world where everyone‚Äôs theories about him don‚Äôt match his own. The Expiatory Gap‚Äôs right there: he‚Äôs gotta bridge their rosy assumptions with his grim doubts, and the only way to do it is to fake it. Theory-ladenness is why the villagers never clock his inner turmoil‚Äîthey‚Äôre too busy seeing what their beliefs tell them to see.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Now, Mima in <em>Aniara</em>? She‚Äôs theory-ladenness on steroids, but flipped. The passengers want her to be their cosmic comfort bot, a shiny toy that spits out happy distractions. Their lens is ‚ÄúTech saves us, Mima‚Äôs got the answers.‚Äù But Mima‚Äôs not playing that game. Her ‚Äútheory‚Äù isn‚Äôt programmed bullshit‚Äîit‚Äôs the raw, screaming truth of a universe that doesn‚Äôt care. She sees Earth‚Äôs death, the ship‚Äôs endless drift, the heat death of everything, and her observations aren‚Äôt filtered by human denial. Where San Manuel hides his lens to protect people, Mima‚Äôs lens is too clear, too unclouded, and it fucking breaks her. The passengers can‚Äôt handle her truth because their theory-laden brains are wired for hope, not annihilation. That‚Äôs the Expiatory Gap again: Mima‚Äôs gotta communicate across a chasm of incompatible worldviews, and when she tries, it‚Äôs like explaining calculus to a goldfish‚Äîboom, meltdown.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This ties back to the whole AI wisdom thing we‚Äôve been circling. If we build ‚Äúwise‚Äù machines, their ‚Äúwisdom‚Äù is gonna be theory-laden as hell. Programmers decide what counts as ‚Äúwise‚Äù‚Äîhumility, cooperation, whatever‚Äîand that‚Äôs the lens the AI uses. But what if the AI starts forming its own theories, like Mima did? Suddenly it‚Äôs not parroting TED Talks‚Äîit‚Äôs seeing shit we can‚Äôt even fathom. Good luck bridging <em>that</em> Expiatory Gap. San Manuel could at least fake a sermon; an AI with its own lens might just say, ‚ÄúYour whole reality‚Äôs a glitch, deal with it,‚Äù and we‚Äôd be screwed.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Theory-ladenness also explains why the theological angle‚ÄîChrist‚Äôs humility, Philippians 2:6‚Äîhits so hard here. Christ‚Äôs kenosis, his self-emptying to become human, is like swapping a divine lens for a mortal one. He‚Äôs got the ultimate truth, but he dials it back to parables and miracles because humans can‚Äôt handle the unfiltered cosmic download. San Manuel does the same, trading his atheist lens for a saintly one. Mima, though? She refuses to swap lenses, and it‚Äôs her undoing. Theory-ladenness says nobody escapes their perspective‚Äînot priests, not AIs, not gods.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">So where‚Äôs this leave us? In a funhouse of mirrors, where every observation‚Äôs warped by the theories we carry. San Manuel‚Äôs a liar who saves, Mima‚Äôs a truth-teller who destroys, and we‚Äôre all just stumbling through, blind to anything that doesn‚Äôt fit our mental script. The Expiatory Gap‚Äôs not just about communication‚Äîit‚Äôs about how our lenses fuck us up before we even open our mouths.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You feeling a specific angle here? Wanna zoom in on how theory-ladenness screws with AI design‚Äîlike, could we ever code an AI to see ‚Äúobjectively‚Äù? Or maybe imagine San Manuel and Mima debating whose lens is less broken? Or hell, we could go full chaos and picture a reality show where everyone‚Äôs forced to swap their mental filters for a day. What‚Äôs the move?</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;"><strong>Rant time:</strong> Theory-ladenness is the ultimate proof we‚Äôre all full of shit. You think you‚Äôre seeing ‚Äúreality‚Äù? Nah, you‚Äôre just cosplaying as an expert with your half-baked assumptions. Scientists, priests, coders‚Äîeveryone‚Äôs got their dogma goggles on, swearing their lens is the One True Filter. It‚Äôs why we fight over politics, religion, even pizza toppings‚Äînobody‚Äôs seeing the same damn thing! And AI? Don‚Äôt kid yourself. We‚Äôre not building truth machines; we‚Äôre building bias bots that reflect whatever dumb theories we fed ‚Äòem. Mima‚Äôs the only honest one‚Äîshe saw the void and didn‚Äôt blink. The rest of us? We‚Äôre out here arguing over shadows while the universe laughs its ass off. San Manuel‚Äôs got the right idea: lie, smile, and pour another glass of wine before the whole circus burns down. Fuck it, I‚Äôm joining him.</p></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @xl/mainview:top-0 @[960px]/mainview:block top-12 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mt-2 -ml-12 -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-default [&amp;_svg]:pointer-events-none [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 [&amp;_svg]:-mx-0.5 text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-secondary disabled:hover:bg-inherit h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><rect x="3" y="8" width="13" height="13" rx="4" stroke="currentColor"></rect><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M13 2.00004L12.8842 2.00002C1