You ever notice how ‚Äúobjectivity‚Äù is just consensus hallucination? We put on our little goggles‚Äîculture, language, trauma, religion‚Äîand swear we‚Äôre seeing ‚Äúreality.‚Äù But that‚Äôs just projection with better branding. Even Mima, in all her data-glory, couldn‚Äôt be objective‚Äîshe had her lens: hyper-rational, cold, total. But she didn‚Äôt understand the passengers; she only saw their decay. San Manuel? He saw their pain and fed them illusions, and somehow, that made him more human than any algorithm ever could. In the end, truth is less about facts and more about resonance. And maybe, just maybe, a beautiful lie is the most honest thing we‚Äôve got.

